{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κτῆσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> (κτάομαι) <b>acquisition</b> (opposed to ἀπόλαυσις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1410a6), κ. τινὸς ποιεῖσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.8, 13; ἡ φιλοσοφία κ. ἐπιστήμης 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 288d; ῥᾳδίαν ἔχει &lt;τὴν&gt; κτῆσιν 4th c.BC: Alcidamas Rhetor “περὶ σοφιστῶν” 5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κατ᾽ ἔργου κτῆσιν according to <b>success in</b> the work, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 230. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (from <i>perfect</i>) <b>possession</b>, λέχους, πλούτου, etc.,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 162, “El.” 960, etc.; κ. ἔχειν τῶν μετάλλων ἐργασίας 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.105; ἡ τῶν χρημάτων κ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 331b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; διὰ τὴν τῶν υἱέων κ. on account of <b>your having</b> sons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ap.” 20b; ἱματίων [prev. author] “Phd.” 64d; φέροντας.. ἀγαθοῦ κτῆσιν οὐδενός 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.308 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἐκ δεσπότου καὶ δούλου [συνέστηκεν] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1277a8 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>holding</b>, opposed to χρῆσις ('using'), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “EN” 1098b32 \">Refs</a>]; <b>ownership</b>, opposed to χρῆσις ('usufruct'), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 237 viii 35, +others; τὰς κτήσεις βεβαίας εἶμεν “IG” 42(1).76.25 (Epid., 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> as collective, ={κτήματα}, <b>possessions, property</b>, διὰ κτῆσιν δατέοντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.158; κ. ὄπασσεν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.62; πατρῴα κ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1290; μετρίης κτήσιος ἐπιμέλεσθαι 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 285; ἡ ἰδία κ. “POxy.” 237 viii 32 (1st c.AD): in _plural_, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.114, etc.; ἀρετῆς βέβαιαι.. αἱ κ. μόναι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 194 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>lands, farms</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 8.19, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 14.29, etc.\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: also in <i>singular</i>, <b>farm, estate,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PFlor. 155.6 (3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8111","accentedUnicode":"κτῆσις","shortDef":"a possession; property","mediumDef":"a possession; property","stepGloss":"a possession","stepTransliteration":"ktēsis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}